# [LOW] gh-74 PayPal plugin would load PayPal button image from HTTP instead of HTTPS

Akeeba Subscriptions 4.1.1
================================================================================
+ Show discounted prices (and pre-discounted amounts in Strappy and Awesome layouts) in the subscription levels page when a user is logged in.
~ Even better workaround for very badly written system plugins which output Javascript without a trailing semicolon and/or newline, leading to Javascript errors. This is not a bug in our software, it's a bug in those badly written plugins and WE have to work around THEIR bad code!
+ gh-55 PayPal plugin: choose the callback URL protocol
# [MEDIUM] gh-56 Percentual surcharge was throwing a fatal error
# [LOW] Entering a coupon code with leading/trailing spaces leads to the coupon code not being recognised
# [LOW] Missing translation string leading to wrong title in the front-end subscription level list page

